# Reference

API references live outside this site:

- **Rust** — [docs.rs/eunoia](https://docs.rs/eunoia/) (rustdoc, the
  authoritative reference for every public type, trait, and function).
- **JavaScript / TypeScript** — type definitions ship with
  [`@jolars/eunoia`](https://www.npmjs.com/package/@jolars/eunoia);
  your editor's "go to definition" / IntelliSense will surface them.
- **Repository conventions** — [AGENTS.md](https://github.com/jolars/eunoia/blob/main/AGENTS.md)
  describes the workspace layout, module organisation, optimisation
  pipeline, and the contract for adding new shape types.

The chapters under [Concepts](/docs/concepts/label-placement/) and
[Bindings](/docs/bindings/wasm-contract/) cover the *why* and the
*how* — use them alongside the rustdoc / tsdoc, not in place of them.
